review_blob: Nice meduim amber color with similar frosty head. Huge hop aroma and taste. Underlying rye flavor is enhanced as the beer warms up a little. Very good brew for hop fans.
beer_name: Bear Republic Hop Rod Rye Ale

review_blob: Nice looking amber color. Too much fake peach flavor, it overwhelms any hope to compliment the underlying ale. Cant identify any pecan flavor. Would be better with just a hint of peach flavor.
Discovered XXXX during vacation in Queensland. Available in almost every restaurant and bar. Light lager with extra hop bitterness. Slightly stinky aroma. Easy to drink on the beach.

Mass produced, classic Bock flavor. Brown pour with a hint toward red. Thin head quickly disappears. Nice smooth mouth feel and mild aftertaste. One of the most popular bar and restaurant beers available in the Houston, TX area.

Light flavor with just the slightest hint of hops. Nice dark color with a thin light tan head. Better flavor  than Shiners flagship brew, their Bock, but not a rich complex beer. Good for light session drinking. Not too bad for a mass produced brew.
